    <br>

    <div id="thumbnails" class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4">
            <div class="thumbnail">
                <img src="img/mobile-icon.png" alt="mobile-icon" height="150" width="200">
                <div class="caption">
                    <h3 class="text-center">Mobile</h3>
                    <p>
                        A mobile device is a small computing device, often with a touch display or a supporting
                        mini keyboard. Major players producing mobile devices include Samsung, Apple, Sony,
                        HTC, LG, and Motorola. Mobile devices can vary in size, ranging from small handheld-sized
                        smartphones to tablets with larger displays. E-readers are also considered mobile
                        devices. Examples of such branded products include Apple's iPhone and iPad, Samsung S4 and
                        Note, Windows Phone and Surface, and Amazon's Kindle and Fire.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-center">
                        <a href="/mobile" class="btn btn-primary" role="button">More on Mobile</a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4">
            <div class="thumbnail">
                <img src="img/bigdata-icon.png" alt="bigdata-icon" height="150" width="200">
                <div class="caption">
                    <h3 class="text-center">Big Data</h3>
                    <p>
                        Big data describes large data sets that are too large for traditional data processing.
                        These days, data is in the petabytes (1 million gigabytes) and analysis, capture,
                        storage, transfer, visualization, and overall manipulation of such large data pools
                        are challenges. The term also refers to predictive analytics or other algorithm approaches
                        taken to extract value from data to further business value, or predict market changes.
                        Major players in the big data field include IBM, SAS, SAP, Oracle, Knime, and RapidMiner.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-center">
                        <a href="/bigdata" class="btn btn-primary" role="button">More on Big Data</a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4">
            <div class="thumbnail">
                <img src="img/iot-icon.jpg" alt="iot-icon" height="150" width="235">
                <div class="caption">
                    <h3 class="text-center">IoT &amp; IoE</h3>
                    <p>
                        Internet of Things (IoT) describes creating a the network of physical objects or "things"
                        embedded with electronic sensors or software that allows it to connect to the
                        Internet. IoT allows ordinary objects to achieve greater value via software
                        that allow for data exchange with manufacturers, operators or other connected
                        devices. Similarly, a new term, Internet of Everything (IoE), hopes to connect these
                        IoT devices to people, processes, data, and other things to develop and
                        create a network of intelligent objects.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-center">
                        <a href="/iot" class="btn btn-primary" role="button">More on IoT &amp; IoE</a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>


